class Solution {
    public String removeOccurrences(String s, String part) {
        while (s.contains(part)) {
            s = s.replaceFirst(part, "");
        }
        return s;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n*m)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: MEDIUM
explanation: This solution uses a while loop to continuously remove the substring until it's no longer found in the string. The replaceFirst method is used to remove the first occurrence of the substring, which is the leftmost occurrence. The time complexity is O(n*m) because in the worst case, we might have to iterate over the entire string for each character in the substring. The space complexity is O(n) because in the worst case, we might have to create a new string that's the same length as the original string.

